      <preamble>
         <formula name="enactingText">
            <p>The Scottish Ministers make the following Regulations in exercise of the powers conferred by section 2(2) of the European Communities Act 1972<noteRef href="#f00001" class="footnote" marker="1"/>, paragraph 1(1) and (3) of schedule 2 of the European Union (Withdrawal) Act 2018<noteRef href="#f00002" class="footnote" marker="2"/> and all other powers enabling them to do so.</p>
         </formula>
      </preamble>
      <body>
         <part eId="part-1">
            <num>PART 1</num>
            <heading>Introduction</heading>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-1">
               <heading>Citation, commencement and extent</heading>
               <num>1.</num>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-1-1">
                  <num>(1)</num>
                  <intro>
                     <p>These Regulations may be cited as the Environment (EU Exit) (Miscellaneous Amendments) (Scotland) Regulations 2019 and come into force as follows—</p>
                  </intro>
                  <subparagraph eId="regulation-1-1-a">
                     <num>(a)</num>
                     <content>
                        <p>as regards this Part and Part 2, on 1 July 2019,</p>
                     </content>
                  </subparagraph>
                  <subparagraph eId="regulation-1-1-b">
                     <num>(b)</num>
                     <content>
                        <p>as regards Part 3, on exit day.</p>
                     </content>
                  </subparagraph>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-1-2">
                  <num>(2)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>These Regulations extend to Scotland only.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
            </hcontainer>
         </part>
         <part eId="part-2">
            <num>PART 2</num>
            <heading>Amendments made under section 2(2) of the European Communities Act 1972</heading>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-2">
               <heading>The Urban Waste Water Treatment (Scotland) Regulations 1994</heading>
               <num>2.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>In regulation 2(1) (interpretation) of the Urban Waste Water Treatment (Scotland) Regulations 1994<noteRef href="#f00003" class="footnote" marker="3"/>, in the definition of “the Directive”, after “last” insert “relevantly”.</p>
               </content>
            </hcontainer>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-3">
               <heading>The Special Waste Regulations 1996</heading>
               <num>3.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>In regulation 6(2)(c) (consignment notes: cases in which pre-notification is not required) of the Special Waste Regulations 1996<noteRef href="#f00004" class="footnote" marker="4"/>, after “schedule 4” in both places it occurs insert “of the 2011 Regulations”.</p>
               </content>
            </hcontainer>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-4">
               <heading>The End-of-Life Vehicles (Storage and Treatment) (Scotland) Regulations 2003</heading>
               <num>4.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>In regulation 2 (interpretation) of the End-of-Life Vehicles (Storage and Treatment) (Scotland) Regulations 2003<noteRef href="#f00005" class="footnote" marker="5"/>, in paragraph (a) of the definition of “vehicle”, after “last” insert “relevantly”.</p>
               </content>
            </hcontainer>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-5">
               <heading>The Water Environment (Register of Protected Areas) (Scotland) Regulations 2004</heading>
               <num>5.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>In paragraph 2(c)(ii) of the schedule (register) of the Water Environment (Register of Protected Areas) (Scotland) Regulations 2004<noteRef href="#f00006" class="footnote" marker="6"/>, after “last” insert “relevantly”.</p>
               </content>
            </hcontainer>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-6">
               <heading>The Foot-and-Mouth Disease (Slaughter and Vaccination) (Scotland) Regulations 2006</heading>
               <num>6.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>In regulation 23(1)(d) (marking of cattle passports) of the Foot-and-Mouth Disease (Slaughter and Vaccination) (Scotland) Regulations 2006<noteRef href="#f00007" class="footnote" marker="7"/>, after “last” insert “relevantly”.</p>
               </content>
            </hcontainer>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-7">
               <heading>The Welfare of Farmed Animals (Scotland) Regulations 2010</heading>
               <num>7.</num>
               <intro>
                  <p>In paragraph 1 (interpretation) of schedule 2 (additional conditions that apply to the keeping of conventionally reared meat chickens) of the Welfare of Farmed Animals (Scotland) Regulations 2010<noteRef href="#f00008" class="footnote" marker="8"/>, in the definitions of—</p>
               </intro>
               <subparagraph eId="regulation-7-a">
                  <num>(a)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>“Regulation 853/2004”,</p>
                  </content>
               </subparagraph>
               <subparagraph eId="regulation-7-b">
                  <num>(b)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>“Regulation 854/2004”,</p>
                  </content>
               </subparagraph>
               <wrapUp>
                  <p>in each case, after “last” insert “relevantly”.</p>
               </wrapUp>
            </hcontainer>
         </part>
         <part eId="part-3">
            <num>PART 3</num>
            <heading>Amendment of secondary legislation relating to withdrawal from the European Union</heading>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-8">
               <heading>The Environment (EU Exit) (Scotland) (Amendment <abbr title="et cetera" xml:lang="la">etc.</abbr>) Regulations 2019</heading>
               <num>8.</num>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-8-1">
                  <num>(1)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>The Environment (EU Exit) (Scotland) (Amendment etc.) Regulations 2019<noteRef href="#f00009" class="footnote" marker="9"/> are amended as follows.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-8-2">
                  <num>(2)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>In regulation 2(6) (new schedule 5 to be inserted into the Water Environment and Water Services (Scotland) Act 2003), in paragraph 19 of schedule 5 of the inserted text, for “are” substitute “is”.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-8-3">
                  <num>(3)</num>
                  <intro>
                     <p>In regulation 3(2) (new paragraph (3) to be inserted into regulation 2 of the Water Environment (Controlled Activities) (Scotland) Regulations 2011)—</p>
                  </intro>
                  <subparagraph eId="regulation-8-3-a">
                     <num>(a)</num>
                     <content>
                        <p>in paragraph (3)(a) of the inserted text, after “is” insert “to”,</p>
                     </content>
                  </subparagraph>
                  <subparagraph eId="regulation-8-3-b">
                     <num>(b)</num>
                     <intro>
                        <p>in paragraph (3)(b) of the inserted text—</p>
                     </intro>
                     <clause eId="regulation-8-3-b-i">
                        <num>(i)</num>
                        <content>
                           <p>after “is” insert “to”,</p>
                        </content>
                     </clause>
                     <clause eId="regulation-8-3-b-ii">
                        <num>(ii)</num>
                        <content>
                           <p>after “interpreted” insert “in”.</p>
                        </content>
                     </clause>
                  </subparagraph>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-8-4">
                  <num>(4)</num>
                  <intro>
                     <p>In regulation 13 (amendment of the Pollution Prevention and Control (Scotland) Regulations 2012)—</p>
                  </intro>
                  <subparagraph eId="regulation-8-4-a">
                     <num>(a)</num>
                     <intro>
                        <p>in paragraph (4)(a)—</p>
                     </intro>
                     <clause eId="regulation-8-4-a-i">
                        <num>(i)</num>
                        <content>
                           <p>in paragraph (j)(v) of the inserted definition of “Chapter <abbr class="acronym" title="3">III</abbr> combustion plant”, omit “other than wood”,</p>
                        </content>
                     </clause>
                     <clause eId="regulation-8-4-a-ii">
                        <num>(ii)</num>
                        <content>
                           <p>in paragraph (b)(v) of the inserted definition of “Chapter <abbr class="acronym" title="4">IV</abbr> plant”, omit “other than wood”,</p>
                        </content>
                     </clause>
                  </subparagraph>
                  <subparagraph eId="regulation-8-4-b">
                     <num>(b)</num>
                     <content>
                        <p>in paragraph (24)(a)(ii), in paragraph 3(a) of the inserted text, omit “law”.</p>
                     </content>
                  </subparagraph>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-8-5">
                  <num>(5)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>In regulation 14(2) (amendment of the Sulphur Content of Liquid Fuels (Scotland) Regulations 2014), in paragraph (j)(v) of the inserted definition of “Chapter III combustion plant”, omit “other than wood”.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
            </hcontainer>
         </part>
